revision.text:
'''Bowin Glacier''' ({{Coord|84|53|S|177|20|E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a tributary [[glacier]], {{convert|5|nmi|km|0}} long, flowing northeast between [[Sullivan Ridge]] and [[Fulgham Ridge]] to enter [[Ramsey Glacier]]. It was named by the [[Advisory Committee on Antarctic Names]] for Commissaryman [[C.F. Bowin]], [[U.S. Navy]], [[Operation Deepfreeze]], 1965 and 1966.<ref name=gnis/>

