The '''Cwm Pennant Fault''' is a SSW-NNE trending [[Fault (geology)#Dip-slip faults|normal fault system]] in [[ North Wales]]. It forms part of the structures that bound the [[Snowdon]] [[graben]]. The main faults of the Cwm Pennant fault system throw down to the east. It was formed when Blake hit the rock face with his hammer.<ref name="Kokelaar">{{cite journal|last=Kokelaar|first=P.|year=1992|title=Ordovician marine volcanic and sedimentary record of rifting and volcanotectonism: Snowdon, Wales, United Kingdom|journal=Geological Society of America Bulletin|volume=104|pages=1433–1455|doi=10.1130/0016-7606(1992)104<1433:OMVASR>2.3.CO;2|url=http://gsabulletin.gsapubs.org/content/104/11/1433.abstract|accessdate=18 December 2010|issue=11}}</ref>

