'''Hatten Schuyler Yoder, Jr.,''' (1921 – August 2, 2003) was a [[geophysicist]] and experimental [[petrology|petrologist]] who conducted pioneering work on minerals under high pressure and temperature. He was noted for his study of [[silicate]]s and [[igneous rock]]s.
==Life== Yoder was educated at the [[University of Chicago]] and the [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]]. He served as the fourth Director of the [[Carnegie Institution of Washington]]'s Geophysical Laboratory, from 1971 to 1986.<ref>[http://www.carnegieinstitution.org/legacy/findingaids/GL-2005-01-General.html Geophysical Laboratory General Files, 1900-Present], ''Shaun Hardy, Ann Mulfort, and Jennifer Snyder'', Carnegie Institution, September, 2005</ref> In 1979, he received the [[Wollaston Medal]].<ref name=GSAobit>{{cite web|last1=Nield|first1=Ted|title=Hatten Yoder Jr, 1921-2003|url=https://www.geolsoc.org.uk/About/History/Obituaries-2001-onwards/Obituaries-2003/Hatten-Yoder-Jr-1921-2003|publisher=The Geological Society of London|accessdate=30 September 2017}}</ref>
He died on August 2, 2003.<ref name=GSAobit/><ref>{{cite news|last1=Levy|first1=Claudia|title=Minerals Researcher Hatten S. Yoder Dies at 82|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/local/2003/08/09/minerals-researcher-hatten-s-yoder-dies-at-82/3a5dc634-0d62-4e4a-b25c-bf2c1cd83983/|accessdate=30 September 2017|work=Washington Post|date=9 August 2003}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Smith|first1=Jennifer|title=Hatten S. Yoder, Jr 1921-2003|url=https://library.gl.ciw.edu/GLHistory/pgyoder.html|website=Geophysical Laboratory|publisher=Carnegie Institution of Washington|date=June 2005|accessdate=2 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Mysen|first1=Bjorn|title=Hatten S.Yoder, Jr. (1921–2003)|journal=Mineralogical Magazine |date=2004 |volume=68 |issue=2 |pages=413&ndash;414 |doi=10.1180/0680413|url=https://pubs.geoscienceworld.org/minmag/article-abstract/68/2/413/85367/hatten-s-yoder-jr-1921-2003?redirectedFrom=PDF|accessdate=2 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Ernst|first1=W. G.|last2=Hazen|first2=R. M.|last3=Mysen|first3=B.|chapter=Hatten S. Yoder Jr., 1921&ndash;2003|title=Biographical Memoirs of the National Academy of Sciences|date=2014|publisher=National Academies Press|location=Washington, D. C.|url=http://www.nasonline.org/publications/biographical-memoirs/memoir-pdfs/yoder-hatten.pdf|accessdate=2 May 2018}}</ref>
==Awards & recognition== * [[Arthur L. Day Medal]], Geological Society of America, 1962<ref>{{cite journal|title=NAS awards to Yoder, Deprit, Johnson, Uyeda|journal=Physics Today|date=August 1972|volume=25|issue=8|pages=75–79|doi=10.1063/1.3070978|url=https://physicstoday.scitation.org/doi/abs/10.1063/1.3070978?journalCode=pto|accessdate=3 May 2018}}</ref> * [[Wollaston Medal]], Geological Society of London, 1979 * [[Roebling Medal]], 1992<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Ernst|first1=W. G.|title=Presentation of the Roebling Medal of the Mineralogical Society of America for 1992 to Hatten S. Yoder. Jr.|journal=American Mineralogist|date=1993|volume=78|page=850|url=http://www.minsocam.org/ammin/AM78/AM78_850.pdf|accessdate=30 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Yoder, Jr.|first1=H. S.|title=Acceptance of the Roebling Medal of the Mineralogical Societyof America for 1992|journal=American Mineralogist |date=1993 |volume=78 |pages=851&ndash;852 |url=http://www.minsocam.org/ammin/AM78/AM78_851.pdf|accessdate=30 September 2017}}</ref>
==Published works== *{{cite book|last1=Yoder|first1=Hatten S.|title=The Geophysical Laboratory|series=Centennial History of the Carnegie Institution of Washington |volume=III |date=2004|publisher=Cambridge Univ. Press|location=Cambridge|isbn=9780521830805}}<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Chinner|first1=Graham|title=Yoder , H. S., J R . 2005. Centennial History of the Carnegie Institution of Washington. Volume III: The Geophysical Laboratory|journal=Geological Magazine|date=16 September 2005|volume=142|issue=04|pages=457|doi=10.1017/S0016756805211159}}</ref>
