{{more citations needed|date=July 2018}}
A '''medical isotope''' is an [[isotope]] used in [[medicine]].

The first uses of isotopes in medicine were in [[radiopharmaceutical]]s, and this is still the most common use. However more recently, [[isotope separation|separated]]  stable isotopes have also come into use.

Examples of non-radioactive medical isotopes are:

* [[Deuterium]] in [[deuterated drug]]s
* [[Carbon-13]] used in [[liver function]] and [[metabolic test]]s <ref>{{cite web|url=http://medical-dictionary.thefreedictionary.com/carbon-13|title=carbon-13|website=thefreedictionary.com}}</ref>

