'''Thermoduric bacteria''' are [[bacteria]] which can survive, to varying extents, the [[pasteurisation]] process.<ref name="indo">{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/farming/dairy/the-heatresisting-bacteria-1388056.html|title=The heat-resisting bacteria|last=Donworth|first=John|date=2008-05-27|work=[[Irish Independent]]|publisher=Independent News and Media|accessdate=2009-08-11}}</ref> Species of bacteria which are thermoduric include [[Bacillus]], [[Clostridium]] and [[Enterococci]].<ref name="glan">{{cite web|url=https://agrilink.ie/MilkNews2007/4241%20Thermoduric%20Bacteria.pdf|last=Murphy|first=Pat|title=Control of Thermoduric Bacteria in Raw Milk Supplies|publisher=[[Glanbia]]|accessdate=2009-08-11|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721121916/https://agrilink.ie/MilkNews2007/4241%20Thermoduric%20Bacteria.pdf|archivedate=2011-07-21|df=}}</ref>

